// Linear dedup scan per match
```
**Fix**: Compile regex once outside loop. Use `toLowerCase().includes()` instead of regex for simple substring match. Input transactions have unique IDs so dedup is unnecessary (or use Set<string> for seen IDs if needed).

### 6. processAll (lines 237-250) — Calls groupByCategory + findDuplicates + topSpenders
This will automatically be faster once the sub-functions are optimized. No structural change needed.

## Correctness Constraints
- All functions must produce identical results (same shape, same values)
- groupByCategory: groups array order = insertion order (first-seen category order)
- findDuplicates: key format is `${userId}|${amount}|${date}`, transactions in order they were found
